Teaching time. Let me tell you about IOA, which is “immediate opposite action.”

You feel tired and terrrible, so you take an immediate opposite action to the feeling: you do something that will build up energy. 

You do *not* double down on the behavior making you feel like trash. 

That’s IOA.

Another example:

You *feel* mad at, and distant from, your spouse. 

What do you do?

You can:

A. Double down on that feeling and distance yourself, shut down, get more mad, stew on negative feelings, get in fights. ie cause more of the *same*

Or 

B. IOA: immediate opposite action: flip the madness and challenge yourself to increase closeness, get present and kind. Ask questions. Hold space. Open up. Work through to a higher level. Generate what you really want: LOVE.

Funny how so many of life’s great improvements come from sensing negative feelings and then doing something to bring good things in versus double down on the pain. 

You can feel the feeling, acknowledge and understand it, but not be controlled by it and make a BETTER CHOICE. 

That’s free will and conscious behavior that changes your life. 

Share with someone today. Every day is a great day to learn and grow. 

Cheering you on today. 
Your coach,
Brendon.

First, this surprises people, upsets others. 

From an interview:

“There’s this myth you have to do all this nonsense to get followers and play to the algorithms. A lot of people do that, because they’ve never really decided who they are or what value and contributions they want to make. 

So their goal is to go viral — that’s actually it for them, there is no goal but views and popularity.

People are shocked you can just do your own thing and you don’t have to play the game.”

Update: I’m told that after a decade apparently I made a meme, about whether you’d choose caffeine or pizza the rest of your life 😂 I wondered this after, well, eating pizza and talking to a fitness expert the next day who was trying to get off caffeine. 

But back to the point. Just do what’s authentic to you, don’t steal or repost just for views and engagement — create and share what’s real for you not what will make you appear more popular. 

Life is SO sweet outside the fear of popularity.

Either you manage the task or the task manages you 👏

The power of intention is SO important and I hope this message serves you on your growth journey.
